						               													<description>Moku Tower&amp;rsquo;s gaming concept originates from our previous product &amp;ndash; Woodas. The theme of Moku Tower is to integrate wood art into tabletop game. It is an unconventional idea that transforms wood art into an artistic, interactive and strategic tabletop game that can be played with a group of friends and/or family members. Moku Tower combines the concept of &amp;quot;timing&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;stacking&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;strategy&amp;quot; into one single game. It allows you to casually mess round, laugh and interact closely with your cool friends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Moku Tower is not only a great party game, it is also an amazing home decoration that can impress your friends. When you are not playing, you can simply display Moku Tower as an art piece. Each game contains 10 different pieces of wooden rocks (includes both big and small) and are made of 8 different types of natural wood material (ash, pine, sapele, maple, walnut, birch, camphor and rosewood). Each of them has different grain, color, weight, texture and even aroma. Also, each piece of wood is exquisitely handcrafted by our wood master. Hence, each of them has its own unique cutting and angle, making Moku Tower one of your most exquisite and unique home decoration.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In respect of the gameplay, in order to win in Moku Tower, you need to be good at timing, stacking and strategy. Within the time limit from the hourglass, players need to stack the wooden rocks to gain points based on the requirements that they draw from the cards. Throughout the stacking process, your opponents can attack you using their &amp;quot;Function cards&amp;quot;. Make good use of the Function cards! It can be the turning point for the whole story. The player who first reaches the accumulative target point wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
